This project involved selecting suitable data for regression problems. 
Once the data has been selected, data preparation is very important. This involves handling missing values, duplicate values, and identifying outliers
After this first step, the next step involves standardizing the columns so that no variable dominates the others and encoding the target variable.
selecting a supervised machine learning classification model which is the following step, involves:
Implementation of at least two classification models. 
Splitting the dataset into training and testing sets.
Train the models on the training data.
Evaluating the models on the testing data using appropriate metrics.
Interpreting the results obtained after evaluation and finally visualized the results.
The last part of our project mainly covers the deployment and monitoring of the model that performed well on a real environment.

